<br>
This list wasn't compiled from a select list of clerics who happened to be friends.  It's made up of the clerics who happen to be showing up in skyfire.  Find out someone is already there, talk to the cleric currently camping.  And decide to participate.  If you know clerics not on the list, then it's cuz they haven't been showing up in skyfire and seeing what's going on, or it's cuz they chose not to get on it.<br>
<br>
It's a choice.  No one is forced to get on the list.<br>
<br>
If you decide to get on it, then you know right up front that you have a bit of a wait for it.  Lots of clerics need him, but we only get a little over 1 a week.  Sony's rules, and we can't change it.<br>
<br>
If that sounds lame to you, and you don't think you should have to wait, by all means start a camp.  Just know that all the people who did try to join in a community effort will be working together to ensure that the cleric next on the list gets the dragon.  Sure, you might get lucky and your guild might be able to mobilize before the current cleric can get enough people there to do it.  But i wouldn't count on it.  In the past 2 months, i only know of 1 cleric who was able to get a force to take down rage before the cleric on the list did.<br>
<br>
Also, understand that this isn't a list being mandated by the guilds.  It belongs to the clerics who were camping it.  Crimson twilight doesn't officially support this list, but we do support our clerics who chose to be a part of it.  Right now, we don't have any clerics on it, but i would imagine that when Rage pops for Boomi, if he doesn't have enough guildmates on to take him down, and we're not in the middle of a raid, you're gonna see people with CT tags dropping into SF.<br>
<br>
So why waste your time telling people it won't work when it already is.  Especially if you're not a cleric.  Fortunately, people with experience are never at the mercy of people with a theory.  <br>
<br>
If you are a cleric ready for rage, you have a choice.  you can choose to wait a bit and get support from others that need him too, or you can go it alone and face all the frustrations clerics have faced since rage was moved to skyfire.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you all, especially Boomi who hopefuly will be the next to plunder the dragon's heart.  <br>
<br>
And a Special Congratulations to Softly.  ~hugs~  You Did It!!!<br>
